@investing・88 Version 0.6.1 has been pushed to GitHub.

Validators: This minor update helps keep the validator loop running in face of network or subtensor errors.

No action is required as all miners and validators will auto update.

@investing・88 Miners: We are adjusting the proposed dynamic emission control (DEC) algorithm as follows, based on evolving data and feedback. This will likely be the final draft, raising to the 3th power while stilling targeting the ~30% inactivity cut-off:

```
burn = (sum(last) / sum(days)) ** 3
if burn > 0.03: validator.scores[0] = sum(scores) * burn / (1 – burn)
```

We’ll leave a couple of more days for long-running miners to adapt. Again if top 50 miners all rebalance once today, it’ll be a non-issue. On the other hand, if inactivity rate remains high after the roll-out, we may change it back to the 2nd power.

Perhaps never. If there are 30 of us here (and I think less), then over time we will choose 1 really working miner, each, and the remaining 220 slots will simply be unnecessary and will hang as dead weight forever.

@InfiniTao By the way, for this reason, I suggest modifying the burn formula so that it takes into account ***days and last*** only among miners with a score > 0.
This will also more quickly make top, but inactive miners move.

@investing・88 Miners:

